---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="CMBT">

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container fade-up">
    <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">Our clinical modality</span>
    <div class="trademark-block">Behold Your Wonder Center<br>Core Messaging Based Therapy™</div>
    <p class="trademark-desc">Core Messaging Based Therapy™ is the proprietary clinical framework developed and offered through the Behold Your Wonder Center for Core Messaging Based Therapy™.</p>
    <h1>A therapy built around<br>the messages that shape you.</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">CMBT™ helps clients uncover, explore, and reframe the internalized beliefs formed through early experience, pivotal relationships, and societal influence.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-center">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-center-inner fade-up">
      <div class="about-center-text">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-dark">About the Center</span>
        <h2>The clinical, educational, and training home of CMBT™</h2>
        <p>The Behold Your Wonder Center for Core Messaging Based Therapy™ serves as the clinical, educational, and training home of the CMBT™ framework. It is the institution through which the modality is practiced, taught, and advanced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-center-list">
        <p class="about-center-list-label">The Center provides</p>
        <ul class="about-center-items">
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Psychotherapy services</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Clinical mental health counseling</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Professional training</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Certification programs</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Educational workshops</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="what">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="what-grid fade-up">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-dark">What is CMBT</span>
        <h2>An integrative approach to lasting change</h2>
        <div class="what-text">
          <p>Core Messaging Based Therapy (CMBT)™ is an integrative therapeutic approach that synthesizes foundational principles from psychodynamic theory, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Emotionally Focused Therapy, and humanistic psychology.</p>
          <p>It centers on helping clients uncover and analyze the internalized messages — and their accompanying emotional echoes — derived from early life experiences, pivotal relationships, and societal norms.</p>
          <p>By identifying these core messages and resonant emotional echoes, clients are guided to reframe and adapt them to foster psychological resilience, improved relational dynamics, and enhanced emotional well-being.</p>
          <p>CMBT's structured yet flexible methodology equips individuals with tools for lasting personal transformation — addressing not just surface-level symptoms, but the foundational beliefs that shape behavior, emotion, and relationship.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="what-features">
        <p class="what-features-label">Key features</p>
        <div class="what-feature"><div class="what-dot"></div><div><p class="what-feature-title">Message-centric focus</p><p class="what-feature-desc">Targets internalized messages as the foundation for cognitive, emotional, and relational struggles.</p></div></div>
        <div class="what-feature"><div class="what-dot"></div><div><p class="what-feature-title">Structured framework</p><p class="what-feature-desc">A clear, phased approach — Discovery, Exploration, Application, and Integration.</p></div></div>
        <div class="what-feature"><div class="what-dot"></div><div><p class="what-feature-title">Holistic integration</p><p class="what-feature-desc">Equally balances cognitive, emotional, and relational components for a comprehensive experience.</p></div></div>
        <div class="what-feature"><div class="what-dot"></div><div><p class="what-feature-title">Client-led exploration</p><p class="what-feature-desc">Therapists act as guides, relying on the client's own data — not imposed interpretations.</p></div></div>
        <div class="what-feature"><div class="what-dot"></div><div><p class="what-feature-title">Depth and sustainability</p><p class="what-feature-desc">Addresses foundational core messages — not just surface symptoms — for long-term change.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="foundations">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="foundations-head fade-up">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">Theoretical foundations</span>
      <h2>Built on four established frameworks</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="found-grid fade-up">
      <div class="found-card"><p class="found-title">Psychodynamic Theory</p><p class="found-desc">Explores how unconscious processes, shaped by formative experiences, influence current behaviors and emotional responses. CMBT adds structure — mapping internalized messages and actively reframing them into healthier beliefs.</p></div>
      <div class="found-card"><p class="found-title">Cognitive Behavioral Therapy</p><p class="found-desc">Provides evidence-based techniques to identify, challenge, and replace maladaptive beliefs. CMBT explores the origins of distorted thoughts as core messages, integrating deeper emotional processing alongside cognitive techniques.</p></div>
      <div class="found-card"><p class="found-title">Emotionally Focused Therapy</p><p class="found-desc">Enhances emotional understanding and regulation within interpersonal contexts. CMBT combines emotional exploration with message reframing — maintaining equal emphasis on cognitive, emotional, and relational components.</p></div>
      <div class="found-card"><p class="found-title">Humanistic Psychology</p><p class="found-desc">Encourages personal growth and self-actualization, emphasizing the individual's capacity for change. CMBT adds a clear framework for message mapping, reframing, and integration within the humanistic spirit of self-determination.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="phases">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="phases-head fade-up">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-dark">The CMBT framework</span>
      <h2>Four phases. One transformation.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="phase-list">
      <div class="phase fade-up">
        <div class="phase-num">01</div>
        <div class="phase-content">
          <h3>Discovery</h3>
          <p>The foundational stage where clients begin uncovering their core messages — deeply internalized beliefs and perceptions formed during early experiences, family dynamics, cultural influences, and significant interpersonal interactions.</p>
          <p>The therapist acts as a compassionate guide, using reflective questioning, active listening, and deep inquiry to help clients unearth and map their core messages in a safe, non-judgmental environment.</p>
          <div class="phase-techniques"><span class="technique-tag">Message mapping</span><span class="technique-tag">Open-ended questioning</span><span class="technique-tag">Pattern recognition</span><span class="technique-tag">Unmet needs exploration</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase fade-up">
        <div class="phase-num">02</div>
        <div class="phase-content">
          <h3>Exploration</h3>
          <p>Building on Discovery, this phase examines the emotional and cognitive impacts of identified core messages. Clients analyze how internalized beliefs actively influence their current thoughts, feelings, and behaviors.</p>
          <p>Clients learn to recognize complex feedback loops where negative messages are reinforced by behaviors and experiences. Breaking these loops is a key goal of CMBT.</p>
          <div class="phase-techniques"><span class="technique-tag">Cognitive reframing</span><span class="technique-tag">Emotionally focused interventions</span><span class="technique-tag">Psycho-education</span><span class="technique-tag">Reflective journaling</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase fade-up">
        <div class="phase-num">03</div>
        <div class="phase-content">
          <h3>Application</h3>
          <p>Clients collaboratively work to reframe negative or limiting messages and disrupt complex feedback loops. The focus is on embedding healthier, adaptive beliefs and behaviors into daily life.</p>
          <p>Through relational repatterning, clients modify core relational beliefs, develop healthier attachment styles, set clearer boundaries, and enhance communication.</p>
          <div class="phase-techniques"><span class="technique-tag">Reframe realignment</span><span class="technique-tag">Relational repatterning</span><span class="technique-tag">Behavioral experiments</span><span class="technique-tag">Role-playing</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="phase fade-up">
        <div class="phase-num">04</div>
        <div class="phase-content">
          <h3>Integration</h3>
          <p>The culminating stage where clients consolidate all previous work. New, healthier beliefs are continuously reinforced through ongoing self-reflection and action planning.</p>
          <p>The therapist transitions to a mentoring role — guiding clients as they embed new perspectives into everyday life and navigate any setbacks with confidence.</p>
          <div class="phase-techniques"><span class="technique-tag">Action planning</span><span class="technique-tag">Ongoing self-reporting</span><span class="technique-tag">Long-term support</span><span class="technique-tag">Reframe realignment</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="concepts">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="concepts-head fade-up">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">Key concepts</span>
      <h2>The language of CMBT</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="concept-grid fade-up">
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Core Messages</p><p class="concept-def">Deeply internalized beliefs derived from early life experiences, pivotal relationships, and societal norms. They serve as the foundation for a client's values, morals, and behaviors.</p></div>
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Emotional Echoes</p><p class="concept-def">Recurring emotional patterns that stem from core messages. These echoes reverberate through time, affecting how a person reacts in present situations.</p></div>
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Message Mapping</p><p class="concept-def">A structured visual exercise tracing the connections between internalized messages, emotional patterns, and present-day behaviors.</p></div>
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Complex Feedback Loop</p><p class="concept-def">The continuous cycle in which deep-rooted negative messages are reinforced by behaviors and experiences, leading to recurring patterns of emotional distress.</p></div>
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Reframe Realignment</p><p class="concept-def">The iterative process of refining and reinforcing healthier messages over time — continuously adjusted through feedback and lived experience.</p></div>
      <div class="concept-card"><p class="concept-name">Relational Repatterning</p><p class="concept-def">Transforming interpersonal relationships by modifying core relational beliefs — fostering healthier attachment styles, clearer boundaries, and improved communication.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="clinical-services">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="clinical-services-inner fade-up">
      <div class="clinical-services-text">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-dark">Clinical services</span>
        <h2>Therapy Using Core Messaging Based Therapy™</h2>
        <p>The Behold Your Wonder Center for Core Messaging Based Therapy™ provides psychotherapy and clinical mental health counseling services utilizing the Core Messaging Based Therapy™ framework.</p>
        <a href="https://beholdyourwonder.clientsecure.me" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule a consultation</a>
      </div>
      <div class="clinical-services-list">
        <p class="clinical-services-label">Areas of support include</p>
        <ul class="clinical-items">
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Women's hormonal mental health</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Emotional overwhelm</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Relationship concerns</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Anxiety</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Life transitions</li>
          <li><span class="center-dot"></span>Identity development</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cmbt-training">
  <div class="container fade-up">
    <span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">For clinicians</span>
    <h2>Train in CMBT</h2>
    <p>Behold Your Wonder offers formal training workshops, supervised clinical practice, and certification programs for licensed clinicians interested in applying CMBT.</p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Inquire about training</a>
      <a href="/services" class="btn-outline-light">View all services</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
.page-hero{background:var(--ink);padding:clamp(64px,10vw,110px) 0;text-align:center}
.page-hero h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:18px;font-size:clamp(24px,3.5vw,42px)}
.page-hero-sub{font-size:clamp(14px,1.8vw,16px);color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);line-height:1.75;max-width:580px;margin:0 auto}
.trademark-block{display:inline-block;font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,38px);font-weight:300;color:#fff;line-height:1.2;margin:16px 0 14px}
.trademark-desc{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,15px);color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);line-height:1.75;max-width:600px;margin:0 auto 36px}

/* ── ABOUT THE CENTER ─────────────────────── */
.about-center{background:var(--cream);padding:var(--pad) 0}
.about-center-inner{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:clamp(40px,6vw,80px);align-items:start}
.about-center-text h2{color:var(--ink);margin:12px 0 16px}
.about-center-text p{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.85}
.about-center-list{background:#fff;border:0.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:clamp(24px,3vw,36px)}
.about-center-list-label{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:18px;display:block}
.about-center-items{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px}
.about-center-items li{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:500;color:var(--ink)}
.center-dot{width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gold);flex-shrink:0}

/* ── CLINICAL SERVICES ────────────────────── */
.clinical-services{background:var(--cream);padding:var(--pad) 0;border-top:1px solid var(--border)}
.clinical-services-inner{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:clamp(40px,6vw,80px);align-items:start}
.clinical-services-text h2{color:var(--ink);margin:12px 0 16px}
.clinical-services-text p{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.85;margin-bottom:28px}
.clinical-services-list{background:var(--ink);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:clamp(28px,4vw,44px)}
.clinical-services-label{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);margin-bottom:18px;display:block}
.clinical-items{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px}
.clinical-items li{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:500;color:#fff}
.clinical-items .center-dot{background:var(--gold)}

.what{background:var(--cream);padding:var(--pad) 0}
.what-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:clamp(40px,6vw,80px);align-items:start}
.what h2{color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:18px}
.what-text{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.85}
.what-text p+p{margin-top:14px}
.what-features{background:var(--ink);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:clamp(28px,4vw,44px)}
.what-features-label{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);margin-bottom:20px;display:block}
.what-feature{display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start;margin-bottom:18px}
.what-dot{width:6px;height:6px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--gold);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:7px}
.what-feature-title{font-size:14px;font-weight:500;color:#fff;margin-bottom:4px}
.what-feature-desc{font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);line-height:1.65}

.foundations{background:var(--ink);padding:var(--pad) 0}
.foundations-head{text-align:center;margin-bottom:clamp(36px,5vw,52px)}
.foundations-head h2{color:#fff}
.found-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:var(--gap)}
.found-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);border:0.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:clamp(22px,3vw,32px)}
.found-title{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);font-weight:500;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px}
.found-desc{font-size:clamp(12px,1.3vw,13px);color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);line-height:1.75}

.phases{background:var(--cream);padding:var(--pad) 0}
.phases-head{text-align:center;margin-bottom:clamp(40px,5vw,60px)}
.phases-head h2{color:var(--ink)}
.phase-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column}
.phase{display:grid;grid-template-columns:80px 1fr;gap:clamp(24px,4vw,48px);padding:clamp(32px,4vw,48px) 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);align-items:start}
.phase:last-child{border-bottom:none}
.phase-num{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(52px,7vw,80px);font-weight:300;color:rgba(245,184,0,0.3);line-height:1}
.phase-content h3{color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:12px}
.phase-content p{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,15px);color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px}
.phase-techniques{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px}
.technique-tag{font-size:11px;background:rgba(30,30,30,0.06);color:var(--ink-soft);padding:5px 12px;border-radius:var(--radius-pill);border:0.5px solid var(--border)}

.concepts{background:var(--ink);padding:var(--pad) 0}
.concepts-head{text-align:center;margin-bottom:clamp(36px,5vw,52px)}
.concepts-head h2{color:#fff}
.concept-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:var(--gap)}
.concept-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:0.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.09);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:clamp(22px,3vw,30px)}
.concept-name{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);font-weight:500;color:#fff;margin-bottom:10px}
.concept-def{font-size:clamp(12px,1.3vw,13px);color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);line-height:1.75}

.cmbt-training{background:var(--gold);padding:var(--pad) 0;text-align:center}
.cmbt-training h2{color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:14px}
.cmbt-training p{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,15px);color:rgba(30,30,30,0.65);max-width:520px;margin:0 auto 32px;line-height:1.75}
.btn-outline-light{border:1.5px solid rgba(30,30,30,0.4);color:var(--ink);font-size:13px;font-weight:500;padding:13px 30px;border-radius:var(--radius-pill);display:inline-block;transition:border-color 0.2s}
.btn-outline-light:hover{border-color:var(--ink)}

@media(max-width:900px){.what-grid,.found-grid,.about-center-inner,.clinical-services-inner{grid-template-columns:1fr}.concept-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.phase{grid-template-columns:60px 1fr;gap:16px}}
@media(max-width:600px){.concept-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>

<script>
const observer = new IntersectionObserver(e => {
  e.forEach(t => { if(t.isIntersecting){ t.target.classList.add('visible'); observer.unobserve(t.target); }});
}, {threshold:0.1, rootMargin:'0px 0px -40px 0px'});
document.querySelectorAll('.fade-up').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
